<h1>Quick start</h1>
<p>All steps you need to make to start using Design System on your site.</p>

<section>
  <h2>1. Install with Yarn</h2>
  <p>As a first step, you need to install Design System libraries using yarn.</p>
  <pre>yarn add @fandom/design-system</pre>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>2. Link to Design System css file</h2>
  <p>In your html file link to styles.css file.</p>
  <Demo @name="quick-start" @language="html" @codeOnly={{true}}>
    <head>
      ...
      <link
        rel="stylesheet"
        type="text/css"
        href="node_modules/@fandom/design-system/dist/css/styles.css"
      >
    </head>
  </Demo>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>3. Start using Design System goodies!</h2>
  <p>Now you can start using DS classes in your application. To check if everything works, just add an example button and check if it is displayed correctly on your site.</p>
  <Demo @name="quick-start-component" @codeOnly={{true}}>
    <Icon @name="alert" @size="small" />
  </Demo>
</section>
